The input for the system should consist of an integer `n`, representing a number, and an array `dislikes`, representing a collection of elements.The condition to be checked by the system is the possibility of splitting everyone into two groups.The dislikes array, where each element `dislikes[i]` represents a pair of people who do not like each other, should be considered by the system.The method should assign a unique identifier to every individual by the system.The method should divide individuals into two separate groups.The condition must ensure that for every pair of individuals in a group, neither person dislikes the other person.The value `true` should be returned by the system if it is possible to split everyone into two groups in this way.The value `false` should be returned by the system if it is not possible to split everyone into two groups without any dislikes within the groups.